022%2C%20with%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge%20in%20the%20background.%3Cp%3EAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussia%20is%20sinking%20its%20own%20ferries%20to%20create%20a%20protective%20barrier%20in%20the%20Kerch%20Strait%2C%20Ukraine%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussia%20is%20doing%20this%20to%20protect%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge%20from%20Ukrainian%20sea%20drone%20attacks%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20one%20expert%20told%20Insider%20this%20won't%20help%20much%20and%20that%20drones%20can%20still%20attack%20the%20bridge.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20sinking%20its%20own%20ferries%20in%20the%20Kerch%20Strait%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20create%20a%20barrier%20that%20will%20protect%20a%20vital%20bridge%20from%20sea%20drone%20attacks%2C%20the%20Main%20Intelligence%20Directorate%20of%20Ukraine's%20Defense%20Ministry%20(GUR)%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2FDIUkraine%2F2712%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20Telegram%20pos%3C%2Fa%3Et%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20GUR%20said%20that%20Russian%20troops%20were%20preparing%20to%20sink%20at%20least%20six%20ferries%20in%20the%20strait%20to%20safeguard%20the%20Kerch%20Bridge%2C%20which%20connects%20Russian-occupied%20Crimea%20to%20the%20Russian%20mainland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20had%20already%20sunk%20the%20first%20vessel%2C%20the%20GUR%20said%2C%20and%20is%20preparing%20to%20sink%20its%20second.%20It%20is%20unclear%20how%20Russia%20is%20sinking%20the%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ukraine%20said%20that%20Russia%20eventually%20plans%20to%20%26quot%3Binstall%20boom%20barriers%20between%20the%20flooded%20ferries%26quot%3B%20to%20form%20a%20defensive%20line%2C%20according%20to%20a%20translation%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kyivpost.com%2Fpost%2F20822%5C%22%3EKyiv%20Post.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20anti-torpedo%20nets%2C%20boom%20defenses%20are%20physical%20barriers%20or%20nets%20that%20either%20encircle%