%20New%20York's%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20International%20Airport%20when%20an%20American%20Airlines%20Boeing%20777%20crossed%20the%20same%20active%20runway%2C%20forcing%20the%20Delta%20plane%20to%20abruptly%20stop%20to%20avoid%20a%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20February%2C%20a%20FedEx%20Boeing%20767%20cargo%20jet%20nearly%20landed%20on%20top%20of%20a%20Southwest%20Boeing%20737%20airliner%20in%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F02%2F06%2Fus%2Ftexas-southwest-fedex-planes-near-collision%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoming%20within%20100%20feet%20of%20each%20other%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20JetBlue%20Airways%20plane%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjetblue-flight-close-call-private-jet-boston-airport-faa-2023-2%5C%22%3Eprivate%20jet%20then%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bclose-call%26quot%3B%20a%20few%20weeks%20later.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20high-profile%20events%20have%20been%20heavily%20reported%20on%20already%2C%20but%20safety%20data%20from%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20and%20analyzed%20by%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20suggests%20they%20are%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairline-close-calls-happening-multiple-times-nyt-investigation-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehappening%20more%20than%20initially%20thought%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F08%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Fairline-safety-close-calls.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETimes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20least%2046%20incidents%20occurred%20in%20July%20alone%2C%20citing%20human%20error%20as%20a%20main%20factor%20in%20the%20near-misses%20%E2%80%94%20including%20one%20in%20which%20two%20planes%20operated%20by%20Frontier%20Airlines%20and%20Southwest%20Airlines%20came%20within%20100%20feet%20vertically%20of%20each%20other%20in%20Denver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20events%20are%20reminiscent%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeadliest-plane-crash-history-pan-am-klm-tenerife-2017-3%5C%22%3Ethe%20deadliest%20plane%20crash%20ever%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tragic%20collision%20of%20two%20Boeing%20747%20jets%20in%20Tenerife%2C%20Spain%20in%201977%20that%20killed%20583%20people.%20It's%C2%A0history%20the%20industry%20doesn't%20want%20to%20repeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20%26quot%3Bcall%20to%20action%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Billy%20Nolen.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e5031631bba700193f86e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20FAA%20acting%20administrator%20Billy%20Nolen%20made%20a%20call%20to%20action%20to%20address%20the%20spike%20in%20near-misses.%3Cp%3EAnna%20Moneymaker%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20March%2C%20regulators%20and%20aviation%20professionals%20have%20come%20together%20to%20mitigate%20the%20concerning%20near-miss%20incidents%2C%20including%20the%20FAA's%20Tuesday%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Frunway-safety-meetings-scheduled-approximately-90-airports%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWASHINGTON%2520%25E2%2580%2594%2520The%2520Federal%2520Aviation%2520Administration%2Cthe%2520FAA%2527s%2520Air%2520Traffic%2520Organization.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannouncement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20will%20hold%20safety%20meetings%20at%20approximately%2090%20airports%20across%20the%20US%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSharing%20information%20is%20critical%20to%20improving%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20Tim%20Arel%2C%20the%20COO%20of%20the%20FAA's%20Air%20Traffic%20Organization%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BThese%20meetings%2C%20along%20with%20other%20efforts%2C%20will%20help%20us%20achieve%20our%20goal%20of%20zero%20close%20calls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20will%20complement%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffaa-launching-safety-review-committee-after-recent-near-crashes-2023-2%5C%22%3EFAA's%20newly-established%20safety%20review%20committee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20safety%20summit%20it%20hosted%20in%20March%20to%20discuss%20ways%20to%20mitigate%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20proximity%20with%20these%20recent%20events%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20close%20those%20aircraft%20got%20to%20one%20another%20definitely%20catches%20everybody's%20attention.%20%26quot%3BAnthony%20Brickhouse%2C%20an%20air%20safety%20investigator%20and%20associate%20professor%20at%20Embry%20Riddle%20Aeronautical%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20these%20events%20are%20so%20high%20profile%20and%20garnered%20so%20much%20attention%20means%20that%20eyes%20are%20really%20on%20it%20and%20that%20exposure%20is%20a%20good%20thing.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Freadout-faa-aviation-safety-summit-breakout-panels%5C%22%3Ebreakout%20sessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20safety%20summit%2C%20officials%20offered%20theories%20like%20inexperienced%20first%20officers%20and%20overworked%20air%20traffic%20controllers%20as%20contributing%20to%20the%20near-disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20pointed%20to%20the%20challenges%20surrounding%20air%20traffic%20controllers%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20as%20a%20root%20cause.%20Not%20only%20are%20a%20majority%20of%20ATC%20facilities%20not%20meeting%20staffing%20thresholds%2C%20but%20controllers%20are%20also%20facing%20fatiguing%20work%20schedules%20that%20could%20impact%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20putting%20safety%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20tired%20employees%20are%20not%20the%20only%20concern.%20Airline%20pilot%20and%20aerospace%20expert%20Kathleen%20Bangs%20told%20Insider%20that%20complacency%20could%20also%20be%20creeping%20in%2C%20especially%20since%20there%20has%20not%20been%20a%20mass%20casualty%20plane%20crash%20in%20the%20US%20since%202009.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20in%20a%20stretch%20of%20historical%20unprecedented%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%2C%20what%20that%20means%20is%20there%20can%20be%20a%20tendency%20for%20any%20system%20to%20get%20complacent%20when%20things%20are%20going%20so%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFlying%20is%20still%20safe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221036%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Delta%20Airplanes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F57a9b271db5ce99d168b5692%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22777%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDelta%20airplanes%20line%20up%20on%20the%20taxi%20way%20after%20Delta%20Air%20Lines'%20computer%20systems%20crashed%20on%20Monday%2C%20grounding%20flights%20around%20the%20globe%2C%20at%20Hartsfield%20Jackson%20Atlanta%20International%20Airport%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20Georgia%2C%20U.S.%20August%208%2C%202016.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FTami%20Chappell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20mounting%20concerns%2C%20runway%20incursions%20are%20statistically%20rare%20considering%20millions%20of%20planes%20take%20off%20and%20land%20every%20year.%20And%2C%20according%20to%20FAA%20data%20revealed%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20rate%20is%20trending%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Faviation-safety-call-to-action%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edown%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20regulators%20work%20to%20address%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20rate%20per%20one%20million%20takeoffs%20and%20landings%20has%20been%20decreasing%20since%202021%20after%20the%202020%20pandemic%20lull%2C%20and%20currently%20sits%20below%202019%20levels%20%E2%80%94%20though%20the%20number%20is%20likely%20to%20change%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20serious%20events%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BCategory%20A%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BCategory%20B%26quot%3B%20incursions%20%E2%80%94%20were%20the%20highest%20in%20January%20at%201.0%20per%20one%20million%20takeoffs%20and%20landings%2C%20but%20fell%20to%200.210%20in%20June.%20The%20lowest%20rate%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Faviation-safety-call-to-action%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFAA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20in%20May%20with%20a%200.00%20rate%20of%20occurrences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20near%20crashes%20have%20also%20prompted%20more%20conversations%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F01%2F18%2Fbusiness%2Fjfk-near-collision-human-error%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechnology%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Austin%20airport%20where%20the%20Southwest%2FFedEx%20event%20occurred%20did%20not%20have%20the%20same%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fair_traffic%2Ftechnology%2Fasde-x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eground%20surveillance%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20alerted%20the%20New%20York-JFK%20controller%20of%20the%20Delta%2FAmerican%20near-crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20has%20since%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Ffaa-invests-over-100m-reduce-runway-incursions-airports%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20safety%20investment%20at%2012%20US%20airports%20to%20reduce%20runway%20incursions%20%E2%80%94%20granted%2C%20Austin%20isn't%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMultiple%20layers%20of%20safety%20protect%20the%20traveling%20public%2C%20including%20Traffic%20Collision%20Avoidance%20Systems%20%5BTCAS%5D%20on%20commercial%20aircraft%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%