6quot%3B%20with%20the%20success%20of%20the%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Flifeandstyle%2F2023%2Faug%2F22%2Ffirst-womb-transplant-uk-hailed-massive-success%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%2034-year-old%20woman%20was%20born%20with%20a%20rare%20condition%20called%20Mayer-Rokitansky-Kuster-Hauser%20syndrome%20(MRKH)%2C%20due%20to%20which%20her%20womb%20was%20underdeveloped.%20It%20affects%20one%20if%20every%205%2C000%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20ovaries%20of%20these%20women%20perform%20functions%20normally%20and%20able%20to%20produce%20and%20female%20hormones%2C%20making%20conceiving%20via%20fertility%20treatment%20a%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20second%20womb%20transplant%20on%20another%20woman%20is%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20next%20month%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20more%20patients%20are%20in%20the%20preparation%20stages%2C%20the%20outlet%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2090%20womb%20transplants%20have%20been%20carried%20out%20internationally%2C%20including%20in%20Sweden%2C%20the%20US%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Turkey%2C%20China%2C%20Czech%20Republic%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Germany%2C%20Serbia%20and%20India.%20About%2050%20babies%20have%20been%20born%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692776220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-05%2Fhb5fjhd8_surgery-generic-unsplash-_625x300_16_May_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fover-the-moon-woman-receives-womb-from-sister-in-uk-first-4321578%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%2034-year-old%20woman%20was%20born%20with%20a%20rare%20condition%20called%20Mayer-Rokitansky-Kuster-Hauser%20syndrome%2C%20due%20to%20which%20her%20womb%20was%20underdeveloped.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fover-the-moon-woman-receives-womb-from